body_html:
FYI, this CL has caused compilation error in tensorflow's nightly builds, e.g.,

tensorflow/compiler/tf2xla/xla_cpu_backend.cc: In function 'bool tensorflow::CpuOpFilter(tensorflow::KernelDef*)':
tensorflow/compiler/tf2xla/xla_cpu_backend.cc:23:11: error: invalid use of incomplete type 'class tensorflow::KernelDef'
if (kdef->op() == "RandomStandardNormal") {
^
In file included from ./tensorflow/core/framework/op_kernel.h:27:0,
from ./tensorflow/core/common_runtime/device.h:41,
from ./tensorflow/core/common_runtime/local_device.h:19,
from ./tensorflow/compiler/tf2xla/xla_op_registry.h:25,
from tensorflow/compiler/tf2xla/xla_cpu_backend.cc:16:
./tensorflow/core/framework/kernel_def_builder.h:27:7: error: forward declaration of 'class tensorflow::KernelDef'
class KernelDef;
^
tensorflow/compiler/tf2xla/xla_cpu_backend.cc:24:9: error: invalid use of incomplete type 'class tensorflow::KernelDef'
kdef->clear_constraint();

See full example logs here.

@ScorpioCPH Can you come up with a quick fix?
